![Episode98.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1578271027234-3NJE2CJ4WIS9N5AMYHZE/Episode98.jpg)

It's the spookiest time of the year, which is the perfect time for some TALES FROM DC BLACK LABEL! Created in 2018, DC Black Label was intended for more mature readers and is filled with unapologetically dark material, starring some of DC's well known characters. In our first adventure **_Joker_** (written in 2008 by Brian Azzarello w art by Lee Bermejo) we follow henchmen Jonny Frost as he chuefers the clown prince of crime around Gotham. In **_Batman: Damned_** mysterious forces are trying to hide the truth from Batman, but can he get to the bottom of it with the help of John Constantine? Join us as we review these twisted tales from DC's Black Label!

If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience, and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
